<br>
i disagree about the 'uber' group being efficient.  a mid 50's group can get insane xp and clear 3 named worth in grid (not even tov quest equipped).  other area's may be a bit more difficult, but the only thing that really matters in CT is level's IMO.  you can do more stuff if you have a full group of 60's with okay gear, than you can with a buncha 55's in really great gear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I was in CT when taunt was broken, wading thru all the garbage while everyone else was whining about how useless warriors are there.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
taunt is pitifully easy to handle in xp groups, even CT before taunt fix.  your group just needs to realize that it's their job to keep agro on you; not your job to keep agro from them.  agro control is a group/raid effort, not lone mystical abillities of weapon procs (though they tend to allow more room for error). <p>--------------<Br>
